WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.660 --> 00:00:03.330
- Sometimes you need more
than just words on a screen

2
00:00:03.330 --> 00:00:06.840
or a verbal description to
really bring an idea to life.

3
00:00:06.840 --> 00:00:07.860
For example,

4
00:00:07.860 --> 00:00:10.650
I could try to describe
a dream I had last night,

5
00:00:10.650 --> 00:00:13.083
or better yet, I could just show you.

6
00:00:18.660 --> 00:00:20.520
So, most of us would jump at the chance

7
00:00:20.520 --> 00:00:23.250
to make our work stand out
with impressive visuals,

8
00:00:23.250 --> 00:00:26.010
but this can be out of reach
if you're not a designer,

9
00:00:26.010 --> 00:00:28.620
but with Gemini, you can
create and transform content

10
00:00:28.620 --> 00:00:30.330
across media types.

11
00:00:30.330 --> 00:00:32.520
For example, you can
build marketing materials

12
00:00:32.520 --> 00:00:34.320
or images for your website,

13
00:00:34.320 --> 00:00:37.440
you can take a report and
turn it into a presentation,

14
00:00:37.440 --> 00:00:40.740
or you can even create a
video with just a prompt.

15
00:00:40.740 --> 00:00:44.010
You can do all of this using
AI's multimodal capabilities.

16
00:00:44.010 --> 00:00:46.500
This means that you can make
a request in one format,

17
00:00:46.500 --> 00:00:47.430
like an image,

18
00:00:47.430 --> 00:00:50.700
and get an output in a
different format, like a video.

19
00:00:50.700 --> 00:00:53.220
For example, you could
give Gemini a text prompt

20
00:00:53.220 --> 00:00:55.203
and get an image in return, like this.

21
00:00:58.230 --> 00:01:00.120
It can also take something like an image

22
00:01:00.120 --> 00:01:02.313
and turn it into a video like this one.

23
00:01:06.330 --> 00:01:08.220
Hey, wanna see something really cool?

24
00:01:08.220 --> 00:01:09.870
It can even take a set of images

25
00:01:09.870 --> 00:01:12.093
and combine them into something else.

26
00:01:17.790 --> 00:01:20.310
So, AI provides a whole
new way of working,

27
00:01:20.310 --> 00:01:23.430
where your ideas and creative
vision define the strategy

28
00:01:23.430 --> 00:01:26.130
and AI can instantly
turn this into reality.

29
00:01:26.130 --> 00:01:28.530
So, what does this mean
for you and your work?

30
00:01:28.530 --> 00:01:30.570
Well, first, you can gain the ability

31
00:01:30.570 --> 00:01:33.450
to generate high-quality
images and videos.

32
00:01:33.450 --> 00:01:35.970
You can add these easily
into any work product

33
00:01:35.970 --> 00:01:37.530
or in your messages to your team,

34
00:01:37.530 --> 00:01:39.570
stakeholders, or customers.

35
00:01:39.570 --> 00:01:41.880
Second, you can expand
your ability to create

36
00:01:41.880 --> 00:01:44.310
with instant format transformation.

37
00:01:44.310 --> 00:01:47.280
Start with something in a Google
Doc, like your messy notes,

38
00:01:47.280 --> 00:01:51.180
or a PDF, a spreadsheet, an
audio file, or another format,

39
00:01:51.180 --> 00:01:52.710
and then from there, you can direct AI

40
00:01:52.710 --> 00:01:55.473
to turn this into a five-minute
presentation outline.

41
00:01:56.430 --> 00:01:59.220
Third, Gemini can give
you on-demand feedback

42
00:01:59.220 --> 00:02:01.890
while you're creating a
draft or piece of content.

43
00:02:01.890 --> 00:02:04.560
Anytime you want, you can ask
Gemini for pointed critiques,

44
00:02:04.560 --> 00:02:08.520
like, "Does this presentation
clearly explain our proposal?"

45
00:02:08.520 --> 00:02:11.400
or, "How might our audience
of first-time home buyers

46
00:02:11.400 --> 00:02:13.440
respond to this video ad?"

47
00:02:13.440 --> 00:02:16.470
Gemini can help you find
potential areas for improvement

48
00:02:16.470 --> 00:02:18.270
and give you tangible suggestions

49
00:02:18.270 --> 00:02:19.833
for how to refine your work.

50
00:02:20.850 --> 00:02:23.460
So, how should you use your
experience and insights

51
00:02:23.460 --> 00:02:24.930
to direct it?

52
00:02:24.930 --> 00:02:27.390
Well, think of AI as your thought partner,

53
00:02:27.390 --> 00:02:28.950
not your replacement.

54
00:02:28.950 --> 00:02:30.480
Review everything it produces

55
00:02:30.480 --> 00:02:33.450
and make sure it matches your
perspective or your brand,

56
00:02:33.450 --> 00:02:35.340
and if you're representing
something as fact,

57
00:02:35.340 --> 00:02:38.520
like transforming a report
into an infographic,

58
00:02:38.520 --> 00:02:41.130
double check that AI got it right.

59
00:02:41.130 --> 00:02:42.870
And always exercise your judgment

60
00:02:42.870 --> 00:02:44.820
by asking yourself if you're using AI

61
00:02:44.820 --> 00:02:46.230
in a way that's appropriate

62
00:02:46.230 --> 00:02:48.183
given the context and the audience.

63
00:02:49.260 --> 00:02:50.910
By the end of this course, you'll be able

64
00:02:50.910 --> 00:02:53.220
to use these techniques
to quickly prototype,

65
00:02:53.220 --> 00:02:54.660
create engaging content,

66
00:02:54.660 --> 00:02:57.090
and get feedback and
pointers about your work.

67
00:02:57.090 --> 00:02:59.430
All right, if you're
ready to start using AI

68
00:02:59.430 --> 00:03:01.140
to bring your ideas to life,

69
00:03:01.140 --> 00:03:02.223
let's get going.